<seg id="231">5.1.1 Intra-Community delivery</seg>
<seg id="232">If the VAT payer makes an intra-Community supply, he is obliged to submit a SH by the 25th day after the end of the calendar quarter.</seg>
<seg id="233">The payer in the Czech Republic provides in the SH summary information on his deliveries of goods to another EU Member State exempt from VAT for the previous calendar quarter.</seg>
<seg id="234">The payer in the Slovak Republic is obliged to state in the SH the value of goods that were exempt from tax and delivered from the Czech Republic to other EU Member States during the calendar quarter.</seg>
<seg id="235">Data on the value of delivered goods are always given in SH in Czech, resp. in Slovak currency broken down by individual tax subjects with the indication of their VAT number under which they were registered in their country.</seg>
<seg id="236">Data on services are not entered in the SH.</seg>
<seg id="237">If the payer in the Czech Republic finds out that he has provided incorrect data in the SH, he is obliged to submit subsequent SHs.</seg>
<seg id="238">In the event that the payer in the SR finds out that the data stated in the SH were incomplete or incorrect, he shall submit a corrective SH before the expiry of the deadline for the submission of the SH, after the expiry of this period he is obliged to submit an additional SH.</seg>
