<seg id="188">5.2 Asylum facilities in the Slovak Republic</seg>
<seg id="189">Asylum facilities are reception centers and accommodation centers.</seg>
<seg id="190">The Municipal Administration manages the Adamov-Gbely, Rohovce, Opatovská Nová Ves and Brezová pod Bradlom residential centers.</seg>
<seg id="191">The total capacity of the reception centers is 470 seats and the residence center 100 seats.</seg>
<seg id="192">The growing number of asylum seekers was addressed by the Municipal Office by establishing a residence center in Gabčíkov in the leased premises of the Slovak University of Technology in Bratislava with a flexible available capacity from 250 to 940 places.</seg>
<seg id="193">According to the concluded contract, the lessee also provides services related to the operation of the center.</seg>
<seg id="194">In this way, the Municipal Office addressed the lack of its own staff.</seg>
<seg id="195">The residential center was also temporarily established in 2002 and 2003 in rented premises in Jaziercie with a capacity of 160 seats.</seg>
<seg id="196">Reception centers had an average occupancy rate of 57% to 62% in the audited period, and an average of 33% to 50% occupancy centers in the audited period.</seg>
<seg id="197">Occupancy varied according to the season and was highest in the last months of the year, when he applied for asylum by a much larger number of applicants compared to other months of the year.</seg>
