<seg id="199">After the completion of the center in Humenné in 2006, the number of seats will increase by another 550 people.</seg>
<seg id="200">5.2.1 Costs of asylum facilities</seg>
<seg id="201">Data on the amount of costs for the operation of asylum facilities are given in Table 4.</seg>
<seg id="202">Their analysis shows that the operation of an asylum facility by another entity that will provide premises and ensure the operation of the facility, including related activities, is one of the ways to ensure at reasonable cost the tasks arising from the stay of asylum seekers in the Slovak Republic.</seg>
<seg id="203">6. Management of financial resources and state property</seg>
<seg id="204">6.1 Management analysis</seg>
<seg id="205">In the Czech Republic, the approved budgeted expenditures of SUZ in 2001 were increased by thirteen budgetary measures by 103,077 thous. CZK.</seg>
<seg id="206">Of which 89 979 ths. CZK (87.29%) were earmarked funds. The majority was intended to address the consequences of the Kosovo crisis (CZK 44,538 thousand) and to provide health care provided to asylum seekers (CZK 38,870 thousand).</seg>
<seg id="207">In 2002, SUZ expenditures were increased by twenty budget measures by 88,362 thousand CZK. CZK.</seg>
<seg id="208">Of which 62 282 ths. CZK (70.48%) were earmarked funds, of which the majority (CZK 53,200,000) was earmarked for health care provided to asylum seekers.</seg>
<seg id="209">In 2003, SUZ expenditures were increased by fourteen budgetary measures by a total of 88,078 thousand CZK. CZK.</seg>
<seg id="210">Of which 82,000 thous. CZK (93.09%) amounted to earmarked funds released from the General Treasury.</seg>
<seg id="211">Amount 51 000 ths. CZK was intended for health care provided to asylum seekers, 24,000 thous. CZK to address the influx of Chechen refugees and 7,000 thous. CZK for the program of humanitarian evacuations of the disabled population of the Republic of Iraq.</seg>
<seg id="212">An overview of the drawing of selected SUZ expenditures in the audited period is given in Table 5.</seg>
<seg id="213">From the above overview, it is clear that the highest part of the expenditure was spent on the provision of services.</seg>
<seg id="214">The amount of expenditures on the purchase of services ranged from 37.07% to 38.23% of total expenditures.</seg>
<seg id="215">Explosive expenditures in this item were expenditures on accommodation and meals for applicants in asylum facilities operated on the basis of a contract, expenditures on medical care provided to asylum seekers and costs for permanent security services providing security in individual asylum facilities.</seg>
