<seg id="217">Last but not least, purchases of materials accounted for a significant share of SUZ's total expenditures (approximately 14%), with food purchases accounting for the highest share (7.61%? 9.83% of total expenditures).</seg>
<seg id="218">In the Slovak Republic, the budget management of the Municipal Office for the provision of migration policy and the asylum process was marked by several budgetary measures that addressed legitimate requirements related to the increase in the number of asylum seekers.</seg>
<seg id="219">The draft and breakdown of the budget in the expenditure part was characterized in particular in 2001 and 2002 by an imbalance between the requirements of the Municipal Office, which was based on an increase in the number of asylum seekers and the need to finance their legal entitlements, and the resources provided.</seg>
