<seg id="845">While in the Czech Republic the payers reported the supply of electricity in accordance with the valid wording of Act No. 235/2004 Coll. as an intra-community supply of goods, from the point of view of the German legislation in force in 2004, it was not an intra-community acquisition, but a taxable supply with the place of supply in Germany.</seg>
<seg id="846">The difference in legal regulations in the Czech Republic was eliminated by the adoption of Act No. 635/2004 Coll., Which amends certain acts in connection with the adoption of the Act on Administrative Fees, effective from 1 January 2005.</seg>
<seg id="847">23. In examining selected intra-Community transactions in cooperation with BRH, it was further found that the Czech payer reported in SH for the 1st to 4th quarter of 2005 an intra-Community supply to a German payer in the total value of CZK 240,411,163 (EUR 8,071,823) and another Czech payer. reported in SH for the same period an intra-Community supply to a German payer in the total amount of CZK 263,470,776 (EUR 8,846,050).</seg>
<seg id="848">According to the information provided by the SAO from the BRH, in both cases it was a supply of electricity.</seg>
<seg id="849">According to the wording of Act No. 235/2004 Coll., Effective from 1 January 2005, in the case of electricity supply, the place of performance is the place where the acquirer has its registered office, place of business or where it has an establishment for which these goods are delivered.</seg>
<seg id="850">Therefore, in 2005, Czech payers should not indicate the supply of electricity to SH.</seg>
<seg id="851">As the two above-mentioned payers reported an intra-Community supply of electricity in SH, the data in VIES were distorted by a total of CZK 503,881,939 (EUR 16,917,873).</seg>
<seg id="852">Conclusion</seg>
<seg id="853">The cooperation met the objectives of the BRH and the SAO.</seg>
<seg id="854">Both SAIs have gained a deeper knowledge of VAT administration systems in the Czech Republic and Germany.</seg>
<seg id="855">The cooperation revealed the differences between the two systems and showed that the legislation in the field of VAT administration differs.</seg>
<seg id="856">During parallel inspections, suspicious cases of intra-Community transactions were identified.</seg>
<seg id="857">It makes sense to check some of them later.</seg>
<seg id="858">Based on the audit findings, both SAIs made recommendations regarding VAT administration.</seg>
<seg id="859">Follow-up to these recommendations should also be part of the follow-up.</seg>
<seg id="860">New experience and knowledge gained through the cooperation of both control institutions are the basis for the successful implementation of the following controls of the VAT administration.</seg>
<seg id="861">Communique</seg>
<seg id="862">The report was prepared in Czech, English and German and signed by the President of the Supreme Audit Office, Czech Republic and the President of the Bundesrechnungshof, Federal Republic of Germany.</seg>
</p>
